Dependencies:
On the master Laptop:
-ROS Kinetic
-ROS joy for X-Box Controller
--sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-joy

On the Pi:
-Rosserial for ros - arduino communication
--Install instructions here: 
--https://www.intorobotics.com/installing-and-setting-up-arduino-with-ros-kinetic-raspberry-pi-3/


Steps to startup MARV
Start ROS core on the master computer
roscore

Set the Master URI on the master
export ROS_MASTER_URI=http://{ip of master}:11311

Set the Master URI on the pi
ssh into the Pi
export ROS_MASTER_URI=http://{ip of master}:11311

Setting up the X-Box controller
plug in / turnon the xbox controller
Deterimine what input the xbox controller is using
$ ls /dev/input/js*
set the rosparam joy_node
$ rosparam set joy_node/dev "/dev/input/js#"

run the Joy node
$ rosrun joy joy_node
